[2] Michigan
Date: 9 Oct 2020
Source: The Horse [edited]
https://thehorse.com/193166/michigan-horse-tests-positive-for-eee/


Michigan Department of Agriculture and Rural Development (MDARD) officials confirmed a Livingston County horse with Eastern equine encephalomyelitis (EEE) on 30 Sep 2020.

The 11 year old standardbred gelding, which had been vaccinated in March 2020, began showing clinical signs on 21 Sep 2020. Signs consisted of fever, depression, ataxia (loss of muscle control), and head tilt.

[byline: Diane E Rice]

