[3] Michigan
Date: 6 Oct 2020
Source: The Horse [edited]
https://thehorse.com/193095/michigan-equine-eee-cases-climb-to-32/


On 25 Sep 2020 MDARD officials confirmed 2 unvaccinated horses with EEE, bringing the state's total confirmed cases to 32 for the year.

The affected horses include a 20 year old Arabian mare in Oakland County and an 11 year old pony mare in Tuscola County. The pony mare is Tuscola County's 1st case in 2020.

Both equines began showing clinical signs on 12 Sep 2020. The Oakland County mare's signs consisted of recumbency (down and unable to rise), and she was humanely euthanized. The Tuscola County mare's signs included ataxia (loss of muscle control) and tremors. She is reported to be recovering.

[byline: Diane E Rice]

