[According to this update, one horse was vaccinated against EEE in March 2020 and began showing clinical signs of EEE in September 2020. Hopefully, this horse received treatment and survived. It is critical to know that immunity to EEE wanes quickly, and in prolonged mosquito seasons, it is recommended to revaccinate against EEE approximately every 3-4 months.

Any unvaccinated horse is extremely susceptible to this disease. Supportive treatment is about all we have, but reading through this report, it seems most of the time, there are poor outcomes for unvaccinated horses. Vaccinating your animals against these diseases is part of responsible animal ownership! - Mod.TG

